<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-12-10T07:16:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-12-10T07:16:00-05:00" n="113" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d113">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/2303</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Roumania, Servia, and Bulgaria</hi>
                                (<persName corresp="#p_VCJ1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Vopicka</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Bucharest</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-12-10T14:00:00+01:44">
                                    <hi rend="italic">December 10, 1915, 2 p. m.</hi>
                                </date>
                                <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received December 12, 7.50 p.
                                m.</hi>]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>197. Political information. Definite arrangements have been concluded
                            between the Austro-German and Roumanian Governments, for the purchase by
                            the former of fifty thousand wagons of Roumanian wheat, only minor
                            details remaining to be adjusted.</p>
                        <p>It is now evident that Roumania will take no action before spring as to
                            participation in the war.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_VCJ1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Vopicka</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>